result.execSummary:
The defendant Rachel A. Peyer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

11:24 am   
Defendant Rachel A. Peyer in court with attorney Patrick L. Cotter.  Sean E. Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Froelich:  Two year DPA offered to the Court on Ct 1 poss of meth.  Ct 2 - plead guilty to Ct 2 - probation 1 year concurrent.  Court must impose DNA same and surcharge $200 on misd   Cotter did not file a plea questionnaire.  Court reviews with defendant.  Court explains the DPA process and possible revocation.  The DPA is contingent on successful completion of probation and vice versa.  Not a vet.  Def pleads guilty to Ct 1 of the Information.  Cotter stips to the facts in the complaint.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS  The court finds the defendant guilty of Ct 1 but withholds JOC.  Def pleads guilty to Ct 2 of the Information.  Cotter stips to the facts.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS  The court finds the defendant guilty and adjudicates def guilty of Ct 2.  Froelich makes sentencing argument.  Def has done assmt and primary treatment and started aftercare.  She has prior theft conviction.  Froelich is recommending DPA on Ct 1 and probation on Ct 2.  Cotter offers DPA to the Court.  Cotter makes sentencing argument.  She is a resident of Transformation House at this time.  Court addresses the defendant.   Judge Boles will not be ordering the DNA surcharge on this case.  
Court orders:  DPA on Ct 1
RE:  Ct 2   S/W Probation 1 year, conditions: court costs, agent to impose conditions on defendant and she must comply with those 
Appeal rights given
